HEADWORD: Wet-bulb thermometer
<hw>Wet-bulb thermometer</hw>. <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>That one of the
two similar thermometers of a psychrometer the bulb of which is
moistened; also, the entire instrument.</def>⟦br⟧
